 MODE n. A general state, usually used with an adjective describing the
state. "No time to hack; I'm in thesis mode." Usage: in its jargon sense,
MODE is most often said of people, though it is sometimes applied to pro-
grams and inanimate objects. "If you're on a TTY, E will switch to
non-display mode." In particular, see DAY MODE, NIGHT MODE, and YOYO MODE;
also COM MODE, TALK MODE, and GABRIEL MODE.